# Bibliography Policy

## Overview

The Divan and the Sword (TDS) maintains a consistent and transparent approach to bibliography and scholarly citation.

This policy explains how references are selected, documented, and maintained throughout the project.

---

## Selection of Sources

Bibliographic references are selected according to scholarly relevance, reliability, and historical significance.

Preference is given to:

- Critical editions
- Peer-reviewed scholarship
- Academic books
- Primary historical sources
- Reputable digital repositories

---

## Citation Principles

The project aims to ensure that every scholarly claim can be traced to appropriate documentary evidence.

References are recorded consistently using recognized academic citation practices.

---

## Bibliographic Metadata

Whenever possible, bibliographic records include:

- Author
- Title
- Publisher
- Publication year
- Edition
- Persistent identifiers (DOI, ISBN, etc.)

---

## Revisions

Bibliographic records may be updated when:

- Improved editions become available.
- Errors are corrected.
- New scholarly evidence justifies revision.

All significant changes are documented transparently.

